g.text: addr3: start point to store the initial 20 numbers - 130 = 100+30
addr5: sub-program for getting the distance - 1600=[MEM[120+0]
addr6: start point to store the 20 absolute distance - 200 = 200+0
addr7: sub-program for getting the absolute distance - 1700=MEM[120+1]
addr8: sub-program for comparing the distance - 1800=MEM[120+2]
addr10: content in Index Register 1 for indirect addressing - 30
addr11: content in Index Register 2 & 3 for indirect addressing - 31
GPR3: store the address for return
